***DML (Data Manipulation Language)***

Used to insert, update, and delete data.

1. INSERT:
    A. Insert Record (Direct):
        INSERT INTO Employee
        VALUES (101, 'Himanshu', 'Nagpur', 50000);
        INSERT INTO Employee
        VALUES (102, 'Soni', 'Mumbai', 60000);
    
    B. Insert Record (Column-wise):
        INSERT INTO Employee
        (EMPID, EMPNAME, EMPCITY, EMPSALARY, PINCODE)
        VALUES
        (103, 'Ayush', 'Hyderabad', 10000, 763122);
    
    C. Insert Using Substitution Variables:
        INSERT INTO Employee
        VALUES (&empid,
                '&empname',
                '&empcity',
                &empsalary,
                &pincode);
    
    Example input:
        Enter value for empid: 104
        Enter value for empname: Mayur
        Enter value for empcity: Goa
        Enter value for empsalary: 10000
        Enter value for pincode: 537272
    
    D. Copy Data from Another Table:
        INSERT INTO Employee1
        SELECT * FROM Employee;

2. UPDATE:
    A. Update Salary:
        UPDATE Employee
        SET EMPSALARY = 55000
        WHERE EMPID = 101;
    
    B. Update City of One Employee:
        UPDATE Employee
        SET EMPCITY = 'Kolkata'
        WHERE EMPID = 103;
    
    C. Update All Rows:
        UPDATE Employee
        SET EMPCITY = 'Nagpur';

3. DELETE:
    A. Delete Specific Employee:
        DELETE FROM Employee
        WHERE EMPID = 104;
    
    B. Delete All Records:
        DELETE FROM Employee;
